727244f-a.text:
Linden Place, at the N.E. corner of 32nd Avenue, formerly Myrtle Avenue, showing a frame dwelling with a lookout tower. This type of home was popular in the latter half of the nineteenth century. Also shown is the north side of 32nd Avenue,
extending east to 137th Street.
P. L. Sperr  March 3, 1932

727246f-a.text:
Linden Place, north from 35th Avenue. The gas tank is at
22nd Avenue. March 12, 1932
P. L. Sperr
